title: SEP Sesam Datastore Status and Usage
agents: sep_sesam
catalog: app/backup
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors SEP Sesam datastores via the SEP Sesam REST API.

 For each datastore the check reports:
 - Operational status (OK / Warning / Critical based on SEP Sesam status codes)
 - Used space as a percentage of total capacity
 - Free, used and total space (shown in service details and graphs)

 Status code mapping: 0 → OK, 1 → WARN, 8 → CRIT.

 Warning and critical thresholds for used space (in percent) can be
 configured via the "SEP Sesam Datastore Usage" rule.

 Requires the SEP Sesam special agent to be configured for the host.

item:
 The name of the datastore as configured in SEP Sesam.

discovery:
 One service is created per datastore. Datastores can be specified explicitly
 in the special agent rule or auto-discovered from the API list endpoint.
